The experimental measured PL transients were modeled using MC simulations of a 3D exciton random walk in a cubic grid (for more details, see ESI, Sect. 6). As the energetic disorder has been obtained earlier, the modeled PL transients (Fig. 6a) were used to extract the exciton hopping time (τ ~ 0.1 ps), which was the only fit parameter. Then the PL quenching efficiencies (Fig. 6b) were calculated using the modeled PL transients. The simulated and experimental results are in good agreement; some discrepancies observed might be attributed to the non-homogenous distribution of PC60BM\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
